reviews.review_text:
A place in my heart for this show In August 1995, I was in the Peace Corps. When I first heard of Jerry's passing, this the first show I listened to afterwords (several times over).

The cheer that goes up within Set II gets me.
Help-->Slip-->Fire

This show is a permanent resident on my MP3 player.

Five-stars for sentimental reasons

my birthday this show took place on my actual birthday...i'm 17 years old and i am a huge deadhead.  the funny thing is my parents aren't and none of my friends are...i turned myself on to the dead i don't recall how though
i've been to see phil lesh, ratdog, and most recently the dead, i have over over 30 shows on my ipod and several more on cd...i was never fortunate enough to see the grateful dead(i wasn't old enough)...it makes me sad that i missed jerry

...anyway this show is great IMO...however i may be biased because it was on my birthday
the bird song is very well played
i love the help>slipknot>fire the crowds response to fire is amazing and best caught on the aud recording
i also love the watchtower>dew sequence
overall a great show
